title: aFRR, Activated Automatic Frequency Restoration Reserves
description: Activated aFRR, also called secondary reserve, is used to restore frequency to the normal band (49.9-50.1 Hz) after the primary regulation (FCR) has stabilised the frequency.

title: aFRR - DK1 Skagerak (Discontinued, please read description)
description:
This dataset is no longer updated. For data after August 2020, please find data here [aFRR, Activated Automatic Frequency Restoration Reserves](https://www.energidataservice.dk/tso-electricity/AfrrActivatedAutomatic) or [aFRR, Automatic Frequency Restoration Reserves, Nordic capacity market](https://www.energidataservice.dk/tso-electricity/AfrrReservesNordic)

Automatic Frequency Restoration Reserves (aFRR), also called secondary reserve, is an automatic 15-minute power control. It shows amounts and prices in Western Denmark. The data is historic, and only includes aFRR through Skagerak (Norway).

title: CO2 Emission
description: The dataset is an updated near up-to-date history for the CO2 emission from electricity consumed in Denmark measured in g/kWh.

title: CO2 Emission Prognosis
description: The dataset is an estimated prognosis following the day-ahead market. The forecast is normally released at 15.00 for the following day, and then adjusted during the intraday trade.

title: Production per Municipality
description: This dataset contains monthly electricity production data in MWh for each municipality, categorized by production from Wind Power, Solar Power, Decentral- and Central Power Plants.

title: Connection points in the electricity grid
description: Connection points in the electricity grid for voltages ranging from 50 to 400 kV.

title: Consumption coverage per municipality long term
description: Future consumption coverage calculated as annual electricity production divided by annual electricity consumption.

title: Consumption coverage per municipality short term
description: Future consumption coverage calculated as the annual production divided by the annual consumption.

title: Consumption Coverage, Location based
description: Explanation of how consumption in DK1 and DK2 is accounted for in the location-based declaration: Import is considered equivalent to local production in this declaration.

title: Consumption Coverage, hourly National statistics
description: This dataset calculates how the consumption is covered by production in DK and connected countries. In the National declaration, Danish production is reserved Danish consumption, and is only used as a political benchmark.

title: Consumption per DK36/DK19 Industry Code per hour

title: Consumption per Grid Area

description: This dataset shows number of active electricity suppliers per grid area and nationwide.

title: Elspot Prices
description: Day ahead spotprices in Denmark (DK) and neighbouring countries.

title: Energy surplus per TSO-station long term
description: Future production surplus as the difference between all production (wind, solar, thermal) and the consumption.

title: Energy surplus per TSO-station short term
description: Future production surplus is calculated as the difference between all production (wind, solar, thermal) and the consumption.

title: Entry/Exit gas flow and quality
description:
The dataset consists of the hourly flow and gas quality values for all entry/exit points in the Danish gas transmission system.

Gas quality naturally varies depending on the origin of the gas. Here is given the hourly unvalidated data for the entry/exit and central points: Nybro (Danish North Sea), Dragør Border (Sweden), Ellund (Germany), Bevtoft (biomethane plant), Ll. Torup (Storage), Stenlille (Storage), Faxe (Poland), and North Sea (Norway)). Gas delivered to Danish consumers may originate from more than one supply source.

title: FCR, Frequency Containment Reserves, DK1
description:
Amount and prices of FCR regulation in bidding zone (Price area) DK1.

Frequency Containment Reserve, FCR, also called primary reserve, must ensure that the balance between generation and demand is restored, stabilising the frequency at close to, but deviating from 50 Hz.

title: FCR N and D, Frequency Containment Reserves, DK2
description:
Frequency Containment Reserve - Normal operation/-Disturbance, FCR N and D, also called primary reserve, is there to stabilize the frequency in the electricity grid in DK2 and in the rest of the Nordic synchronous area, in the event of a frequency dip/jump.
Energinet procures FCR-N, FCR-D up and FCR-D down capacity reserve in collaboration with Svenska Kraftnät in daily auctions where part of the required volume is procured two days before the day of operation, D-1 early (former D-2) and the remaining part is procured the day before the day of operation, D-1 late (former D-1).

For data after January 2021, please find data in either links: [Regelleistung.net - Datencenter](https://www.regelleistung.net/apps/datacenter/tenders/?productTypes=PRL&markets=BALANCING_CAPACITY,BALANCING_ENERGY&date=2022-05-09&tenderTab=PRL$CAPACITY$1) or [FCR, Frequency Containment Reserves, DK1](https://www.energidataservice.dk/tso-electricity/FcrDK1).

title: Gas Accumulated System Balance
description: The GasAccumulatedSystemBalance shows the accumulated system balance (ASB).

title: Gas hourly allocation and nomination
description:
This view shows the hourly allocation/nomination for each entry/exit point and other points in the Danish Transmission System.

For the Joint Exit Zone and Renuwable Energy Ressource Entry points the allocation is availabe with a delay of 2 hours. Nominations are not provided for these points.

For all other points the allocation is  present at 15:00 the day before. Technically speaking the allocations are nominations until the hour is closed for changes.

The values listed are for informational purposes only and are not suited for settlement purposes.

Note: A new field Direction (Entry/Exit) was added 11-09-2023 after 11:00.

title: Gas booked by product
description: The data set contains information of the original sold capacity per product type: yearly, quarterly, monthly, daily and rest of day.

title: Gas Capacity Usage
description:
Gas Capacity Usage shows the capacity, available and booked capacity at each entry/exit point in the Danish gas market.

The view is updated frequently during the gas day.

For the information on interruptible terms please refer to the interruptible column description.

title: Gas composition and quality for transmission
description: The dataset contains the hourly non-validated gas composition and other gas quality parameters for the Danish Transmission as measured at Energinet’s gas quality measuring station in Egtved.

title: Gas composition and quality for transmission, monthly
description: Gas quality data for the Danish transmission grid that is representative for gas delivered from the transmission grid. The data are validated but the data cannot be used for billing purposes. The basis of the dataset is hourly values and the maximal and minimal value is therefore respective the maximal and minimal hourly value.

title: Gas composition and quality for transmission, yearly
description: Gas quality data for the Danish transmission grid that is representative for gas delivered from the transmission grid. The data are validated but the data cannot be used for billing purposes. The basis of the dataset is hourly values and the maximal and minimal value is therefore respective the maximal and minimal hourly value.

title: Gas Daily Balancing Price
description:
This views shows the prices used for the invoicing of the daily sale og purchase of balance gas after 01-10-2022.

Prices will remain unvalidated until the invoicing of balancing gas. Non-valid balancing gas prices should provide Shippers with an indication on what to expect.

Energinet are in dialogue with the Danish Utility Regulator and Green Power Denmark on how to handle the final imbalance invoicing for October and November 2022, on days where the market players’ balancing task has been particularly difficult.

title: Commercial gas amounts
description: Daily commercial gas amounts in the Danish gas market. The data is accumulated from the previous gas day.

title: Gas monthly neutral price DKK/kWh

title: Gas Daily System Commercial Balance before 01-10-2022
description:

title: Gas Daily System Commercial Balance

title: Herfindahl - Hirschman Index (HHI) per Grid Area

title: Realtime Market (Discontinued, please read description)
description:
This dataset is no longer updated. Use instead [Regulating and Balance power, overall data](https://www.energidataservice.dk/tso-electricity/RegulatingBalancePowerdata)

Maintaining balance between consumption and production in the electricity system and fulfilling contracts with e.g. Sweden or Norway may require an up or down regulation of production and consumption in the Danish electricity system (east or west). For this purpose a so-called regulating power market is established as a common market for the Nordic countries.

Storage capacity provides information about total and reserved capacity for

* Injection on firm terms
* Injection on interruptible terms
* Withdrawal on firm firms
* Withdrawal on interruptible terms

title: Storage utilization
